<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="628" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2790</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Moscow</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PDC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Poole</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]<note n="1" xml:id="d628fn1">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_667">p. 667</ref>.</note></seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-09">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 9, 1918</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 26, 5.05
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5. … Massacre of Russian citizens by Bolshevik government continues.
                                Shootings at Moscow number about 150 nightly. More than 1,000 people
                                have been shot in retaliation for attempt on <persName corresp="#p_LNVU1">Lenin</persName>. I have protested personally
                                to <persName corresp="#p_CGV1">Chicherin</persName> pointing out
                                that Bolshevik cause totters on verge of complete moral bankruptcy.
                                    <persName corresp="#p_WMA1">Wardwell</persName> has written
                                strong protest in the name of American Red Cross. But Commissariat
                                Foreign Affairs has no control and but small influence over
                                extraordinary commission which is carrying on the carnage. The
                                situation is tragic beyond words and it is difficult to see from
                                what quarter relief may come. …</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PDC1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Poole</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>